# .github/CODEOWNERS
# This file is used to automatically assign reviewers for pull requests.
# More details: https://docs.github.com/en/repositories/managing-your-repositorys-settings-and-features/customizing-collaborators-and-permissions-in-your-repository/about-code-owners

# Each line specifies a path pattern followed by one or more owners.
# The owners can be GitHub usernames (prefixed with @) or team names inside an organization (e.g. @org/team-name).

# By default, make @Praneeth-Suresh the owner/reviewer for all files in the repository.
*       @Praneeth-Suresh

# To add specific reviewers for specific paths, define them below.
# Note: The last matching pattern has the highest precedence.

# Examples:
# 1. To make @another-reviewer own the markdown topic files (where content is added):
# /src/content/topics/      @another-reviewer

# 2. To make a team or multiple reviewers own the GitHub workflows configuration:
# /.github/workflows/       @Praneeth-Suresh @another-reviewer

# 3. To make a designer/frontend developer own the global style sheets:
# /src/styles/              @designer-username
